<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="82" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4131/10–1145: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-11T18:00:00-05:00">October 11, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>9039. On October 11 US–UK Commercial Policy Committee ratified agreed
                                positions, which had been worked out earlier in combined
                                subcommittees, regarding <hi rend="italic">a</hi>) procedure for
                                holding proposed conference on trade and employment in a manner
                                designed to avoid unilateral decision by US as to whether non-United
                                Nations should be invited to conference; <hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                                export taxes; <hi rend="italic">c</hi>) state trading; and <hi rend="italic">d</hi>) subsidies. There remain for consideration
                                subjects of cartels, exchange controls, and preferences. It is hoped
                                that an agreement in subcommittee regarding first two of these will
                                be reached shortly.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>